🐌⚔️ The real thing (quick + accurate)

Many slugs (like banana slugs) are simultaneous hermaphrodites:
	•	each individual has both male and female reproductive organs

When two meet, they often:
	•	engage in a kind of “fencing” behavior
	•	each tries to inseminate the other first

Why?

Because:
	•	being “male” (donor) = lower cost
	•	being “female” (receiver/egg layer) = higher energy investment

So they’re essentially negotiating:

Who takes on the higher-cost role?

